verbose_text: Males had increased BMI (23.36 kg/m <sup> 2 </sup> vs. 21.07 kg/m <sup> 2 </sup>, p < 0.05) and insulin level (23.60 mU/l vs. 10.76 mU/l, p < 0.05), while females exhibited increased waist (77.5 cm vs. 71.8 cm, p < 0.05) and hip (96.7 cm vs. 92.9 cm, p < 0.05) girth compared with the offspring of uncomplicated pregnancies.
